      "citation_id": "[CITATION_5]",
      "span_text": "Cell senescence is defined as the irreversible form of cell cycle arrest that can be induced by p53/p21 or p16INK4a/pRb tumor suppressor pathway activation. 40) Senescent cells exhibit a senescence-associated secretory phenotype (SASP) and excrete various chemokines and ECMdegrading enzymes such as matrix metalloproteinases. Although myofibroblasts are cells with high proliferative and ECM-producing capacity, senescent myofibroblasts are in irreversible cell cycle arrest and degrade ECM via SASP."
